content.div:
This is sure to brighten your day: On the red carpet for the premiere of his new movie, Dr. Seuss' The Lorax, a condom fell out of Zac Efron's pocket.


--

New mom Beyonce is looking fine in her new House of Dereon ad.

--

Sacha Baron Cohen has not been banned from the Oscars - yet.

--

It's on! Hunger Games tickets went on sale this week, and have already broken Twilight: Eclipse's pre-sale record.

--

Sad news: The actor who played Mr. Kruger on Seinfeld has been hospitalized after an apparent suicide attempt.

--

Congrats to Private Practice star Caterina Scorsone, who's expecting her first kid.

--

Russell Brand is reportedly "finding himself" - in bed with lots of women.

--

Paula Abdul has been ordered to pay $900,000 US to a woman who slipped in her driveway.

--

Producer The-Dream has revealed that it was Rihanna's idea to invite Chris Brown to guest on "Birthday Cake."

--

George Clooney's mom has been tapped to dish dirt on her famous son during the Oscar per-show. Fingers crossed she brings baby pictures!

--

Ryan Phillippe has backed out of CBS' upcoming cop drama.

--

News that J.K. Rowling is writing a new book made the Internet explode yesterday.

--

Selena Gomez is feeling the love: she got a heart tattooed on her wrist.

Check back to Dose.ca throughout the day for your entertainment fix.
